The paper deals with the application of deep convolutional neural networks for volumetric medical image segmentation, specifically for brain parcellation. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of dilated convolution and residual connections, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions uncertainty estimation, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
